{
  "texts": [
    "The STD of R Hα fluctuation (R STD Hα",
    ") is also calculated for the sample since it is commonly adopted in the literature.",
    "In order to examine the relationship between the values of R EXT Hα and R STD Hα, in Figure 11 we show the distribution of the ratio value of R STD Hα /R EXT Hα with N obs for the stellar sources in the MRS time-domain sample of solarlike stars employed in this work (data points in blue; same stellar source sample as employed in Figure 7).",
    "As a reference, we also simulate the R STD Hα /R EXT Hα distribution by using a normal distribution model and through the Monte Carlo approach (the sample size of the simulated distribution being 10 5 for each of the N obs values).",
    "The simulated model distribution of R STD Hα /R EXT Hα is displayed in light gray in the background in Figure 11."
  ]
}